# General Workflow

## Project Structure
- All projects live in `~/Cursor/projects/` (frontend, backend, fullstack, automation, etc.)
- Shared configs in `~/Cursor/shared/configs/`
- N8N workflow exports in `~/Cursor/projects/n8n-workflows/`
- N8N config (URL + API key) at `~/Cursor/shared/configs/n8n-config.json`

## LinkedIn
- Work ONLY with the **UntLab** LinkedIn account (organization ID: 111598449, credential: "UntLab LinkedIn account")
- NEVER touch any other LinkedIn account (Najaf or any other)
- N8N workflow for UntLab: `LinkedID_UntLab_autopublisher` (ID: HwO0UZOsWuBuOEhZ2UHR5)

## Code Standards
- Write clean, readable code with meaningful variable names
- Functions should do one thing and do it well
- Handle errors properly — never silently swallow exceptions
- Use environment variables for secrets (never hardcode)
- Create `.env.example` to document required env vars

## Git
- Use conventional commits: `type(scope): description`
- Create `.gitignore` before first commit
- Sync finished projects to GitHub: `gh repo create name --private --source=. --push`

## When Creating New Projects
- Always scaffold in the correct `~/Cursor/projects/` subfolder
- Initialize git immediately
- Add project-specific `.cursor/rules/` if needed
